3Ô∏è‚É£ Subscription Types

Monthly: 51.61% churn (highest)

Annual: 46.22%

Quarterly: 44.05%

Insight: Monthly subscribers generate more revenue per person but are the most unstable.

4Ô∏è‚É£ Usage & Customer Behavior

Usage Frequency:

Low frequency: 54.9% churn

High frequency: 43% churn
Insight: Engagement strongly predicts retention.

Support Calls:

Few calls ‚Üí 25% churn

Medium ‚Üí 60.9% churn

High ‚Üí 60.8% churn
Insight: üî¥ High support interaction indicates frustration and poor experience.

Payment Delays:

Longer delays correlate with higher churn.

Female loyal customers have the highest payment delays: 17.62
Insight: Payment frustrations or financial strain contribute to churn.

üìå Recommendations
Insight	Recommendation
-Retention leak after 24 months	Introduce loyalty offers, mid-term check-ins with surveys & incentives, personalized retention messages during renewal periods
-Female customers churn higher	Build customer personas, improve features for female use cases, provide female-focused onboarding messaging
-Monthly subscribers churn highest	Launch monthly loyalty program, auto-renew incentives, flexible subscription ‚Äúpause‚Äù options
-Low-frequency users	Trigger ‚Äúlow-usage nudges‚Äù with recommended content, offer customizable reminders, improve onboarding tutorials
-High support interaction	Identify top 3 issues causing calls, launch quick-fix improvements, add proactive in-app guidance
-Payment delays	Offer flexible payment options, reminders, and financial support for at-risk customers

‚úÖ Key Takeaways:

-Mid- and long-term loyal customers are the primary churn risk.

-Female and older customers require tailored engagement strategies.

-Subscription type and usage patterns are strong predictors of churn.

-Support interactions and payment delays are actionable signals for intervention.
